Prerequisites:
1.Python
2.Install the required Python libraries:
pip install pandas

Steps to Run the Script:

Download the Files:
Ensure the following files are in the same folder:
updatejson.py (the script)
config.json (the JSON file to be updated)
input.csv (the CSV file with the data to update the JSON)

Open Terminal/Command Prompt:
Navigate to the folder where the above files are located.

Run the Script:
Use the following command to run the script, updating the JSON based on the environment (DEV or PROD) specified in the CSV:
# ./updatejson.py --env <ENVIRONMENT> --json <PATH_TO_JSON> --csv <PATH_TO_CSV>

# ./updatejson.py --env DEV --json ./config.json --csv ./input.csv
